    "Our study suggests one key takeaway: The answers from ChatGPT are indeed rated sufficiently correct to assist students of Bachelor and Master levels on a wide range of questions in natural science and engineering; Yet ChatGPT lacks skills we expect from students.",
    "A striking difference between what faculty members expect from student answers and answers from ChatGPT is a critical reflection and a clear understanding of the concepts used.",
    "While in 37 cases participants rate the reply as \"completely incorrect\", ChatGPT did not generate a reply that states it does not know the answer in our study.",
    "This suggests that there might be knowledge gaps and a lack of critical reflection of ChatGPT about its answers.",
    "A possible explanation for this could be ChatGPT's underlying model, which, as stated by the developers, sometimes produces plausible-sounding but incorrect answers (https:// openai."
